KOTLIN COLLECTIONS

Array: Mutable but has Fixed Size

List
- an ordered collection with access to elements by indices

Set
- collection of unique elements
- a group of objects without repetitions

Map
- set of key-value pairs.
- useful for storing logical connections between objects
ex. an employee's ID and their position

Immutable Collections: Read Only Operations
Immutable List: listOf
Immutable Map: mapOf
Immutable Set: setOf

Mutable Collections: Read and Write
Mutable List: ArrayList, arrayListOf, mutableListOf
Mutable Map: HashMap, hasMapOf, mutableMapOf
Mutable Set: mutableSetOf, hashSetOf